title: N.H. Football: Eichman (4 TDs), Merrimack whip Londonderry
text:
N.H. Football: Eichman (4 TDs), Merrimack whip Londonderry Eagle-Tribune 
LONDONDERRY — Sophomore Joe Eichman rushed for four touchdowns and Merrimack whipped Londonderry 41-7. 
The Tomahawks (4-2) threw a scare into No. 1 Pinkerton last week and Friday night they showed it wasn’t a fluke. 
Eichman rolled to a 27-0 lead midway through the third quarter. Londonderry (2-4) got on the board late in the third on a 44-yard Jake Stevens pass to David Weidenfeld (3 catches 91 yards). 
Gary Richard had 10 solo tackles and an assist for the Lancers, who Friday are at Spaulding (0-5 heading into Saturday’s game). 
Merrimack 41, Londonderry 7
